		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">RAID 5 makes me wanna <a href="http://www.baarf.com/" class="postlink">BAARF</a>.</div><br />I think that RAID6 should generally be favored over RAID5, but saying that parity-based RAID levels should never be used (or, according to one of the presentations from that site, that RAID10 should ALWAYS be used) doesn't make sense.  In the real world, one usually needs to make trade-offs between cost/performance/reliability.  If I need a large amount of storage for an application with low IO requirements, RAID10 is probably not the best choice.  Certainly not from a cost perspective.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
