	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: SSD died after dropping laptop</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />RAID protects from some hardware failures, downtime. But it's an exact mirror, so doesn't save you from non-hardware-caused data loss. Separate backup protects you from hardware failure, and from accidentally deleting files, filesystem corruption, etc. Off-site protects from theft, house fire, etc. Also, incremental backups protect from undetected corruption that gets copied to the more recent backup(s).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


